===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|martren}}, {{m|enm|martryn}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}} {{m|fro|martrine||marten fur}}, from {{etyl|odt|en}} {{m|odt|*marþrin||of marten fur}} (compare {{etyl|dum|-}} {{m|dum|martren}}), from {{m|odt|*marþra||marten}} (compare {{etyl|nl|-}} {{m|nl|marter}}), from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*marþuz}} (compare Low German {{m|nds||Mort}}, West Frisian {{m|fy|murd||polecat}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|mearþ||shrew}}), originally 'wedding' (compare {{etyl|gme-cgo|-}} {{m|gme-cgo||marzus|wedding}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*martus||bride}}. More at [[marry]]. For sense development, compare {{etyl|it|-}} {{m|it|donnola||weasel}}, from {{m|it|donna||lady}}, {{etyl|el|-}} ''nyfítsa'' 'weasel', from ''nymfē'' 'bride'.

